Definition: conducted with or marked by hidden aims or methods
Example: clandestine intelligence operations; cloak-and-dagger activities behind enemy lines; hole-and-corner intrigue; secret missions; a secret agent; secret sales of arms; surreptitious mobilization of troops; an undercover investigation; underground resistance
Synonyms: cloak-and-dagger, hole-and-corner, a, hugger-mugger, hush-hush, secret, surreptitious, undercover, underground, noun, group, conducted, with, or, marked, by, hidden, aims, methods, intelligence, operations, activities, behind, enemy, lines, intrigue, missions, agent, sales, of, arms, mobilization, troops, an, investigation, resistance
Category: adj.all
